# Git Deploy Workflow

Primary remote: `origin` → `https://github.com/MohammedGamalll/PH-PIXEL-SYSTEM.git` (branch `main`).

Vercel production auto-deploys from `main` pushes to that repo.

## After completing code changes

When the user asks for implementation (not question-only or review-only tasks):

1. Run `git status` and stage only relevant files — never commit `.env`, `.vercel/`, or `lib/db/scripts/.clone-dumps/`.
2. Create a concise commit message focused on **why**.
3. Push to `origin main` immediately after commit.
4. If push fails with auth error, use `GITHUB_TOKEN` from `.env` (never print or commit the token):

```powershell
$token = (Get-Content .env | Where-Object { $_ -match '^GITHUB_TOKEN=' }) -replace '^GITHUB_TOKEN=',''
git push "https://x-access-token:${token}@github.com/MohammedGamalll/PH-PIXEL-SYSTEM.git" main
```

5. Confirm Vercel deployment started (Git push triggers build on `ph-pixel-system-alpha.vercel.app`).

## Do not

- Push to `muabushama` remote unless explicitly requested.
- Force push unless the user explicitly approves replacing remote history.
- Commit secrets (`.env`, service role keys, DB passwords).
